   Communications-PerCom-Annual, Washington, DC, MAR 17-21, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc; IEEE Computer
   Society; IEEE Computer Society Technical Committee on Parallel
   Processing; IEEE Computer Society-Technical Committee on Computer
   Communications; University of Maryland Baltimore County; George Mason
   University; National Science Foundation; University of Maryland
   Baltimore County College of Engineering and Information Technology; New
   Jersey Institute of Technology},
Abstract = {The rise of 6G networks and the exponential growth of IoT devices pose
   significant challenges in resource management and energy efficiency,
   particularly in dense smart city environments. This paper explores the
   optimization of IoT networks using LoRa technology, focusing on
   enhancing energy efficiency through the discrete Firefly Algorithm,
   which dynamically adjusts key communication parameters such as spreading
   factor (SF) and transmission power (TP). Tested in realistic scenarios
   with thousands of devices, multiple gateways, and interference, the
   proposed method improved received power by up to 40\%, which
   consequently results in efficient energy consumption, thus making it a
   promising solution for urban IoT networks.},
